<article>
    <h1>WINDY AULIA, 38, CRE&#xAD;ATIVE DI&#xAD;REC&#xAD;TOR AT HARPER&#x2019;S BAZAAR SIN&#xAD;GA&#xAD;PORE&#xD;&#xA;AND HER WORLD</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201218/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-18"><time>2020-12-18</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>“Lately, I’ve been busy with Christ­mas projects for Harper’s Bazaar Sin­ga­pore and Her World, for both the print and dig­i­tal ver­sions.</p>
    <p>I’ve been stay­ing in­spired and en­ter­tained dur­ing this busy pe­riod by watch­ing YouTube, Net­flix, HBO Go, Ama­zon Prime – and the list goes on.</p>
    <p>I’ve also been read­ing in­ter­est­ing books via the National Li­brary</p>
    <p>Board’s Mo­bile app.</p>
    <p>The bot­tom line is, I’ve been us­ing my iPhone and Air­Pods a lot. That’s why I’m eye­ing the Na­tive Union Wire­less Charg­ing Dock (£75.79 or S$137) from Mr Porter. It’s sleek and stylish and can charge both de­vices at one go.</p>
    <p>An­other thing I’d love to see un­der­neath my Christ­mas tree is a Burberry pantsuit (price un­avail­able, above right) in the sup­plest of wool and the brand’s sig­na­ture checks.</p>
    <p>It’s ver­sa­tile and proper with­out be­ing too prim – I call that ‘when ease meets for­mal’. I can wear the whole out­fit for the evening or match the jacket with jeans for a smart-ca­sual look.</p>
    <p>Now, if only I knew where to send a spe­cial re­quest to Mr Claus.</p>
    <p>My fam­ily has noth­ing spe­cial planned for Christ­mas, but we might do a bar­be­cue beef feast at home.</p>
    <p>We are still de­cid­ing whether to or­der from steak­house Pi­can­has’ or Decker Bar­be­cue – they do dif­fer­ent bar­be­cue styles, but are equally de­li­cious.”</p>

